#: org.kde.hashomatic.metainfo.xml:24
msgid "Verifying that a file you downloaded or received is actually the one you were expecting is often overlooked or too time-consuming to do. At the same time, it has become very easy to get your hands on a file that has been tampered with, due to the mass increase of malicious webpages and other actors."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#. +> trunk6
#: org.kde.hashomatic.metainfo.xml:30
msgid "This tool aims to solve that. Hash-o-matic comes with a simple &amp; clean UI, allowing anyone, from any age and experience group, to generate, compare and verify MD5, SHA-256 and SHA-1 hashes."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#. +> trunk6
#: org.kde.hashomatic.metainfo.xml:35
msgid "Hash-o-Matic also support verifying a file with the help of a PGP signature."
msgstr ""

